More and more parents use people tracking devices to control their children
Fear for children leads more and more people to think about controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for the tracking of vehicles, can also follow the movement of people and contribute thus, for example, in case of the disappearance of the nine-year-old Anička Janatková.
Currently, the device has the approximate size of a cylinder box, but soon it will be reduced to the size of a clock.
A lot of people feared the case of the missing Anička and began informing about the available means to better protect their children.
Even at the expense of invading your privacy.
“We all try to tell ourselves that it’s not about spying, but another means to decrease the chances of a tragedy,” says Petr Pilin from Macro Weil, one of the suppliers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
“I recognize that, in certain cases, such devices can be abused, for example if they are put into someone’s pocket without their knowledge, but we have not yet met with such cases.”
“Most customers actually buy it for security reasons,” adds Pilin.
In their opinion, children should always know what the "box" serves and how it is used in the event of emergency.
Children's psychologist Dana Bočková warns about the fact that if the child doesn't want to take it, he'll just throw it out.
“Even younger children show great creativity when deliberately losing certain things if they want to prevent them from being controlled.”
“Before, parents trusted tremendously in mobile phones, but these could be turned off as easily as the tracking device,” Bočková says.
In your opinion, it is controversial whether in case of attack such a device is really useful.
“If it’s a prepared kidnapping, the author will almost always check if the child carries any kind of electronic device that can reveal his location.”
“Today is the phone.”
"After extending the use of the tracking devices, they will also search for them, since their sale will be done with a lot of advertising."
“In such cases, criminals always go a step ahead of the police,” says the psychologist.
However, he adds that such devices can help in the case of an improvised attack by a pedophile.
According to Robert Čech of the company RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both vehicles and people, even if, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, its presence can serve as a help.
"The device can be configured so that it regularly sends the position after a given period."
"If you suffer damage, at least it will facilitate the last position of the person in question."
“The most expensive devices carry an integrated inclination meter, so if the person simply scratches and remains immobile, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question,” says Čech.
