For years, the simplification of business standards has been a declared goal of all governments.
However, compared to the rest of the world, the situation improves especially in the Czech Republic.
According to the World Bank, from the point of view of the conditions to have a company, Czech Republic lies in the 74th place, i.e. eight positions worse than last year.
The Absurdez Competition of the Year was held for the first time in 2006 and is repeated in the same way each year.
Anyone can indicate any administrative or bureaucratic absurdity each year between April and the end of September, when the contest is closed.
