In the year 2007, what most annoyed people was the businessman’s obligation to communicate with a three-day in advance to the business office of the permanent operation zone, the intention to go with a place to a fair or exhibition.
This obligation was eliminated in the new industrial law.
The obligation that ended in second place in number of votes in 2007, i.e. the communication to the work office by its foreign workers of the work trips of up to 30 days, was eliminated in the law of the so-called green card.
The third is the defeated.
