“It is our duty to gather these broken pieces so that we can understand.”
The center produced the first text book approved by the government on the Red Jemers, called "A History of Democratic Kampuchea", of 75 pages.
It was distributed at Anlong Veng in June as a supplement to the secondary school history textbook of the Ministry of Education, which contains less than four pages about the Red Jemers.
As in most of Cambodia, the young people of Anlong Veng know few details about the Red Jemers, despite the city’s bond with the regime.
