I am changing the rules for visa.
People will have to go to the Visa Applicants Service centers before their interview in the Consular Section; the cost will be lower and the waiting time.
From 10 January 2011 the procedure for the processing of a visa in the U.S. Embassy and Consulates will be changed.
With the new procedure, most applicants will have to go to the Visa Applicants Service (ASC) centers before their interview in the Consular Section.
ASC staff will take the applicant’s biometric information, which will be reviewed by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will have certain advantages for aspirants, among which are:
The total cost of processing the visa will be lower, it will no longer be necessary to make a payment to concert the date, another payment to process the visa application and another more for the messaging service to deliver the document.
The applicant will only make a single payment that will cover the three services.
The current rate will remain unchanged: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for requested visa cases (including temporary workers visa) and $390 for traders and investors visa.
People who wish to renew their visa will not have to go to an interview with the Consular Office, but will only go to the nearest ASC where they will present their documents and take their footprints.
Because biometric information will be taken in the ASC, applicants who require a second date to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain in this less time than in the past.
Also, those who apply for visa at the Consulates in Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the extra service fee of $26.
For further information about the new visa application procedure, visit the following page http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
